claim.claim-text:
17. A computer readable storage device comprising instructions that, in response to execution, cause a system comprising a processor to perform operations, comprising:
verifying identity information of a device that transferred a connection from a set of source network devices of a source network to a set of target network devices of a target network, wherein the identity information comprises a data rate supported by the device;
comparing a subscribed quality of service parameter for a packet data session of the set of target network devices with an original quality of service parameter of the set of source network devices, wherein the original quality of service parameter comprises a first data rate supported by the set of source network devices and the set of target network devices supports a second data rate that is higher than the first data rate;
initiating a modification procedure to negotiate a modified quality of service parameter for application to the connection to the set of target network devices, wherein the modified quality of service parameter comprises a third data rate selected from the data rate supported by the device, the first data rate, and the second data rate; and
sending the modified quality of service parameter and the third data rate to the device.
